cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with the deployment of a wireless robotic network and the analysis of interference power. This falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses information theory (cs.IT) to formulate a lower bound on the number of orthogonal codes required for interference-free communication. The analysis of the network structure and performance requirements falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the simulations conducted in the paper involve multimedia (cs.MM) data transmission.
